parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause coolant leaks, overheating, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine fires.
symptoms: coolant dripping onto exhaust system and other components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause hesitation, stalling, and loss of power, leading to safety hazards and potential accidents.
Transmission issues can cause hesitation, stalling, and loss of power, leading to safety hazards and potential accidents.
symptoms: transmission shifting with a thump or loud bang
transmission missing shifts and going into neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and safety hazards.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. In some cases, the vehicle may surge forward or backward, resulting in damage to property or other vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when the driver is braking or shifting gears. The acceleration may be accompanied by a sudden increase in engine RPM. In some cases
the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the driver is applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The cruise control system may malfunction
causing the vehicle to accelerate suddenly and unexpectedly. In some cases
the system may fail to disengage when the vehicle is turned off

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Floor Mat Interference with Accelerator Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Floor mat interference with the accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The floor mat may become trapped under the accelerator pedal
causing the pedal to stick and resulting in unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or lurch forward, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: humming or winding sound from underneath the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to accelerate unintentionally, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the transmission and clutch system can cause the vehicle to hesitate, lurch, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The close proximity of the brake and accelerator pedals can cause accidental acceleration when attempting to brake, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: pressing the gas pedal instead of the brake pedal
or surging forward when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a delay in stopping or a loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor
or the vehicle continues to accelerate when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the disc brakes due to environmental factors can cause the brake pads to fail to retract completely, leading to continuous rubbing on the rotors, heating, and warping, which can affect vehicle safety.
The failure of the brake system can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: or the vehicle surging forward when applying the brakes.
